<title>CZECH REPUBLIC: Czech c.bank says CZK at -2.0 pct as &quot;reasonable&quot;.</title>
<headline>Czech c.bank says CZK at -2.0 pct as &quot;reasonable&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>PRAGUE 1997-05-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Czech central bank (CNB) on Wednesday said its open market operations were hitting their mark, with the crown showing stability, adding that two percent below its basket midpoint was a reasonable level.</p>
<p>&quot;Now the crown is at two percent which is reasonable so it looks like the operations are working, we see mainly stability and maybe some expectations are changing,&quot; Ludek Niedermeyer, a CNB bank board member, told Reuters.</p>
